        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): ignore stale running rows after terminal chat",
        "body": "## Summary\n- keep a terminal current chat session from being revived by stale `sessions.list` or `sessions.changed` rows with `status: \"running\"`\n- preserve real newly started runs by allowing newer `startedAt` rows after the previous terminal `endedAt`\n- add regressions for stale list rows, stale websocket rows, and late stale websocket rows after the run-status toast clears\n- include a lint-only cleanup for redundant `image-tool.ts` provider-registry casts required by current `pnpm check:changed`\n\nFixes #86939.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Webchat can flip back from `Done` to permanent `In progress` when a stale current-session row with `status: \"running\"` arrives after the terminal chat event has already cleared the local `chatRunId`.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw checkout at PR head `27ff166db9d6`, Linux, Node `v22.22.0`, real controller/runtime modules executed via `node --import tsx`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Created a current dashboard session row already terminal (`status: \"done\"`, `hasActiveRun: false`, `chatRunId: null`), applied a stale `sessions.changed` payload with `status: \"running\"` and `hasActiveRun: true`, then checked `hasAbortableSessionRun()`.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the runtime command:\n\n```text\nenvironment=node v22.22.0 platform=linux\nbeforeAbortable=false\n{\n  \"applied\": true,\n  \"change\": \"updated\"\n}\n{\n  \"key\": \"agent:main:dashboard\",\n  \"kind\": \"direct\",\n  \"updatedAt\": 3,\n  \"hasActiveRun\": false,\n  \"status\": \"done\",\n  \"startedAt\": 1,\n  \"endedAt\": 2,\n  \"sessionId\": \"sess-main\"\n}\nafterStaleEventAbortable=false\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The stale running update was applied for metadata freshness but normalized back to `hasActiveRun: false` and `status: \"done\"`, so abortable chat UI stays disabled after the terminal run-status toast clears.\n- **What was not tested:** No live browser dashboard was driven manually; the proof uses the real session controller and chat abortability predicate, with UI/controller regression coverage below.\n\n## Verification\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts --pool forks --maxWorkers=1 --reporter=tap`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/app-chat.test.ts --pool forks --maxWorkers=1 --reporter=tap`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts --pool forks --maxWorkers=1 --reporter=tap`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/agents/tools/image-tool.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/sessions.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n\nNote: running all three recommended UI test files in one `run-vitest` invocation timed out after 240s in this local environment with no failure output, but the three files passed when run individually.\n",
